The evidence with the title 'Redistricting moderates out of Congress - The Washington Post ' says May 17, 2012  ... And not a single newly drawn district would be more competitive. Forty years ago, when i was an intern on the Hill, about half of congressional districts were genuinely competitive. Today, only about 10 percent of House races on Cook Political Report are listed as “toss-ups” or “lean” to one party. 
